18/04/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The European Commission (EC) anticipates greater concrete results from Bulgaria in fighting organised crime and high-level corruption, Bulgaria's new Minister for European Affairs, Gergana Grancharova, was told during her first official visit to Brussels on Tuesday (April 17th).
She met with European Parliament officials, EC Justice Commissioner Franco Frattini, and Bulgaria's EU commissioner, Meglena Kuneva, who is in charge of consumer protection.
In other news Tuesday, Bulgaria announced plans to hold a nationwide census in 2011, as part of a wider EU headcount.
The last census, conducted in 2001, counted 7.9 million Bulgarians.
(Monitor, Sega - 18/04/07)
